name: Safe Zone No.1 (Digital Editon)
description: This artwork is from a series called Morphine, which was later renamed the Safe Zone. The Safe Zone is driven out from the dark era of the artist’s life when he was struggling with the addiction problem. A passive period that isolated the artist in his safe corner, a period that was just a consumption, without any action.  This lived experience was an inspiration for the artist to extend his encounter toward the world, to a large part of contemporary societies. Societies that do not act, have no action and only consume in their safe zone, in corners of their home.
